"{\"uid\": \"thetab.com-2024-08-16-elon-musk-and-jk-rowling-could-face-up-to-five-years-in-prison-if-imane-khelif-wins-her-lawsuit\", \"text\": \"The Olympic boxer named the two in her cyberbullying lawsuit after gender dispute  Elon Musk and JK Rowling could face up to five years in prison or a \\u00a3214,000 fine if Imane Khelif wins the cyberbullying lawsuit she has filed in Paris after the Olympics, where she was relentlessly called a man online. Elon Musk and JK Rowling were named when Imane Khelif filed a cyberbullying lawsuit against X in Paris this week - and could face prison if the lawsuit is won by the boxer.  According to theDaily Mail, if Imane Khelif is successful with her lawsuit the repercussion for cyberbullying under French law are prison sentences ranging between two to five years or fines between \\u00a326,000 and \\u00a339,000. If parties are found guilty instead of online hate speech, the fines can range from \\u00a369,000 to \\u00a3214,000.  Nabil Boudi, Khelif's Paris attorney, has explained that the lawsuit is filed against X itself, which \\\"ensure[s] that the 'prosecution has all the latitude to be able to investigate against all people,\\\" including anyone hiding behind a fake name or an anonymous account - to make sure that everyone can be investigated for any cyber attack on Khelif and her gender.  The International Olympic Committee backed Imane Khelif fully when she found herself in a huge controversy that saw prominent figures like JK Rowling, Elon Musk and Donald Trump claim she was a man. The IOC said \\\"scientifically, this is not a man fighting a woman\\\" and it has been proven that she was born female, and does not identify as intersex as others have claimed. JK Rowling posted a picture of Imane Khelif after her defeat of Italian boxer Angela Carini to her millions of followers saying Khelif was \\\"enjoying the distress of a woman he's just punched in the head.\\\"  But what does this Imane Khelif lawsuit mean for those prominent figures like JK Rowling who are not French residents? Boudi explained that the lawsuit could have international implications for those outside France, explaining \\\"it could target personalities overseas,\\\" and pointing out that \\\"the prosecutor's office for combating online hate speech has the possibility to make requests for mutual legal assistance with other countries.\\\"  Boudi also said: \\\"What we are asking is that the prosecution investigates not only these people but whoever it feels necessary. If the case goes to court, they will stand trial.\\\"  The Tab approached representatives of JK Rowling and they declined to comment on the matter.  \\u2022'Women have been targeted': Those close to Imane Khelif defend her after false gender row  \\u2022'It can destroy people': Imane Khelif emotionally asks for bullying towards her to end  \\u2022'I want to apologise to her': Angela Carini is saddened by backlash towards Imane Khelif  Featured image viaShutterstockbefore edits.  Scan the mo to help a bro  The judge ruled he shared responsibility for the deaths and injuries  Except they progressively get further away\\u2026  The changes will impact module choices and assessments  Some more psychoanalysis based off of your music taste  Everyone get excited  Fans screamed, 'OUT, OUT, OUT!' as audience members were removed by staff  I guess we will never know  There is actually a deep meaning  They glossed over the references to US politicians  It's a lot of words  The judge ruled he shared responsibility for the deaths and injuries  Except they progressively get further away\\u2026  The changes will impact module choices and assessments  Some more psychoanalysis based off of your music taste  Everyone get excited  Fans screamed, 'OUT, OUT, OUT!' as audience members were removed by staff  I guess we will never know  There is actually a deep meaning  They glossed over the references to US politicians  It's a lot of words  Trends | Harrison Brocklehurst  Trends | Kieran Galpin  Trends | Ellissa Bain  Trends | Kieran Galpin  Entertainment | Kieran Galpin  Entertainment | Kieran Galpin  Entertainment | Kieran Galpin  Trends | Ellissa Bain  Entertainment | Harrison Brocklehurst  Entertainment | Hebe Hancock\"}"